<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-4851] SessionStore.fetch(key) is a performance bottleneck</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4851</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When flushing the &lt;tt&gt;CachingSessionStore&lt;/tt&gt; we need to search for the previous value for a session. This involves searching each open RocksDB segment. The code ends up doing a call  &lt;tt&gt;Segments.segments(0, Long.MAX_VALUE)&lt;/tt&gt; this results in approximately 3 million gets on a &lt;tt&gt;ConcurrentHashMap&lt;/tt&gt; of which all but 3 of them will be hits. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Change this code to restrict the segmentIds to search just to the available set.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
